# ------------------------------------------------------------------ #
#  Optional configuration for the Personal Boardspace.
#
#  You do NOT need this file to run the app. `docker compose up -d --build`
#  works with zero configuration — a strong SESSION_SECRET is auto-generated
#  and persisted in the data volume on first boot.
#
#  Create one ONLY if you want to override a default below:
#     cp .env.example .env
#  Never commit the real .env.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------ #

# OPTIONAL. Pin the session secret instead of using the auto-generated one.
# Must be >= 32 chars. Handy if you want the same secret across multiple hosts.
#     openssl rand -base64 48
# SESSION_SECRET=

# OPTIONAL. Only needed if Server Actions get rejected behind a proxy that
# changes the Host header. localhost and correctly-forwarded hosts work without
# it. Comma-separated, scheme included, no trailing slash.
#     ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://todo.example.com
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=

# OPTIONAL (defence in depth). If set, every request must carry the header
# `X-Proxy-Secret: <this value>` or it's rejected (health check exempt).
# Use this if you put a reverse proxy in front that can inject a static
# header. Without a reverse proxy, leave it unset.
#     openssl rand -hex 32
# TRUSTED_PROXY_SECRET=

# Do NOT set in production. Local-only escape hatch to test a production build
# over http://localhost (disables Secure/__Host- cookies).
# ALLOW_INSECURE_COOKIES=true

# OPTIONAL. Force Strict-Transport-Security (HSTS) to be sent on every
# response, even over plain HTTP. The default is to send HSTS only when the
# request is detected as TLS-secured (https:// URL or x-forwarded-proto=https
# from a trusted proxy). Set this to "on" only if you want to force HSTS on
# plain HTTP — useful for testing the HSTS path, NOT for production.
# STRICT_TRANSPORT_SECURITY=on
